Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Peel @carrots{4}(peeled), then cut on a diagonal into 1-inch-thick pieces. Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating greens and whites. In a #medium bowl{}, mix @ground beef{10%ounce}, scallion whites, @meatloaf spice blend{1%tablespoon}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, and @white pepper{1/4%teaspoon}. Season with @salt{1%tsp}(to taste) and a pinch of @pepper{pinch}.

> We sent more panko and pepper than this.

Shape beef mixture into two 1-inch-tall loaves. Gently press down to flatten slightly. Toss carrots in another medium bowl with a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{4%teaspoon}, @dried thyme{1/2%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper. Place carrots on one side of a #baking sheet{} and meatloaves on other. Bake in oven on upper rack until meatloaves are cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Mashed Potatoes ==

Meanwhile, cut @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce}(cut into 1/2-inch cubes). Place in a #medium pot{} with a big pinch of @salt{big pinch} and @water{enough to cover by 1 inch}. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, about ~{15%minutes}, then drain and return to pot. Place over low heat, then add @sour cream{2%tablespoon} and @butter{2%tablespoon}. Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with salt and pepper. Keep covered off heat.

== Onion Topping ==

While potatoes cook, halve, peel, and very thinly slice @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled, and very thinly sliced). Add slices to a #large pan{} with a large drizzle of oil and place over medium-high heat. Cook, tossing often, until lightly browned and softened, about ~{5%minutes}. Stir in a splash or two of @water{a splash}. Let water evaporate, ~{1-2%minutes}. Repeat adding and evaporating water once or twice more until onion is deeply browned.

== Assembly ==

Once meatloaves and carrots are done, sprinkle meatloaves with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}. Return to oven. Let cheese melt, ~{1-2%minutes}.

  set aside. Add @beef stock concentrate{1%unit} and @water{1/4%cup} to pan with onion. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Let reduce, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from heat, then stir in @butter{1%tablespoon}. Season with salt and pepper.

Give sauce a taste and stir in @?sugar{1/4%teaspoon} if you prefer a sweeter flavor. Divide potatoes, carrots, and meatloaves between plates. Spoon onion and its sauce over meatloaves. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.